eu.trentorise.opendata.jackan.model

Class CkanResourceBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.trentorise.opendata.jackan.model.CkanResourceBase
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CkanResource

    public class CkanResourceBase
extends Object
    A Ckan Resource describes with metadata a physical file, which may reside outside ckan. Resources are part of CkanDataset. In DCAT terminology, a Ckan Resource is a DCAT Distribution. CkanResourceBase holds fields that can be sent when creating a resource,, while CkanResource holds more fields that can be returned with searches. This class initializes nothing to fully preserve all we get from ckan. In practice, all fields of retrieved resources can be null except maybe url.
    Since:
    0.4.1
    Author:
    David Leoni

      • getLastModified

        public String getLastModified()
        Jackan note: this field should represent the timestamp of the last update of the resource *data*, not metadata. I think it's set by extensions and harvesters. Notice Ckan always refers to UTC timezone in CkanClient.CKAN_TIMESTAMP_PATTERN format, so this field probably should follow the same format.

      • getName

        @Nullable
public String getName()
        Human readable name, i.e. "Apple Production 2013 in CSV format". Not to be confused with CkanDatasetBase.name which instead is lowercased and intended to be part of the url. Notice we found name null in data.gov.uk datasets... i.e. unclaimed-estates-list , taken from this dataset search (They use description field instead)
